Me: (We're back here. The park. That grey afternoon.)
Sam: I should get going. My train's at four.
Me: Already? You only just got back.
Sam: I'm tired. I'm tired of everything.
Sam: You included.
Me: Wait — please, don't leave.
Sam: Oh. So you suddenly care now?

